---
description: Responsive behavior and visual fidelity requirements
alwaysApply: false
globs:
  - "src/**/*.{css,scss,ts,tsx}"
---

responsive-visual:
- Start from mobile content priority, not desktop shrinkage.
- Verify at 360, 390, 768, 1024, 1440, and 1920 CSS pixels.
- No horizontal overflow.
- Hero must remain readable without depending on text over a busy face or subject.
- Do not hide essential content on mobile.
- Convert dense grids into ordered stacks with preserved meaning.
- Avoid fixed heights for text-heavy sections.
- Reserve image dimensions to prevent layout shift.
- Use art direction when one crop cannot serve mobile and desktop.
- Keep primary CTA reachable early without creating intrusive sticky behavior.
- Capture before/after screenshots for major visual work.
